[2] Texas (statewide)
Date: Fri 20 Dec 2013
Source: Brownwood News, Brownwood/Brown County Health Department (BBCHD) report [edited]
http://www.brownwoodnews.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=14057


Pertussis, also known as whooping cough, is on a historic rise according to health officials. As of 16 Dec 2013, Texas has reported 3482 pertussis cases to the CDC for 2013 and has reported 3 deaths due to pertussis. Texas has not seen case numbers this high since 1959. Over the previous 3 weeks, there have been 3 cases of pertussis reported to the Brownwood/Brown County Health Department. The Brownwood/Brown County Health Department encourages the citizens of Brownwood and Brown County to check vaccination records and get vaccinated for this disease.

Pertussis is most harmful to young babies and can be deadly. It is very important that pregnant women and caregivers of babies maintain their Tdap [combined tetanus, diphtheria, and pertussis] vaccination.

[Byline: Cliff Karnes]

