[4] Ohio (Clark County)
Date: Sun 8 Dec 2013
Source: Springfield (OH) News Sun [edited]
http://www.springfieldnewssun.com/news/news/local/clark-pertussis-cases-still-rising/ncDhn/


The outbreak of pertussis cases in Clark County follows a national trend that shows that whooping cough rates reached a 50-year high in 2012. Clark County has had a record 117 confirmed and suspected cases of pertussis since 1 Oct 2013, up from 98 before the Thanksgiving holiday [28 Nov 2013], Clark County Combined Health District Director Charles Patterson said. Patterson expressed frustration Friday [6 Dec 2013] after announcing the pertussis outbreak continued to climb in the area. "There is some frustration because, if one family with the disease has extended family of 10 people, and each of them spread it to 5 or 10 people, it makes it difficult to stop," Patterson said.

In 2013, Ohio has seen a 20 percent increase in reported pertussis cases, compared to 2012. As of 2 Nov 2013, there had been 901 cases reported in 2013, compared with 742 on the same date in 2012. Clark, Madison, Pickaway, Licking, Delaware, and Richland counties have the highest rates of the disease statewide, according to the Ohio Department of Health.

[Byline: Tiffany Y Latta]

